data.title: The Queen
data.text: I really do love The Dairy Queen.  Great soft serve...But also the best Chicken FIngers and french fries too..

data.title: Busy Place
data.text: This is a very clean and friendly place. The workers knew the patrons by name. They were extremely friendly and helpful. Thoroughly enjoyed our visit here. Excellent employees

data.title: Brings me back to my childhood
data.text: Love this place, staff always friendly place is clean and keep on top of, love the fact they have lunch specials too.

data.title: Nice For The Kids!
data.text: Vacation to Jupiter, included nightly visits for the kids. Very crowded, bu the line moves quickly. Great for the adults that they sell Orange Julius! Haven't had one since the 1980's.

data.title: Typical DQ
data.text: Long lines due to a problem with the register. My blizzard was almost gone before I paid for it. The staff was very nice and the quality as expected.

data.title: Friendly Option for Frozen Treats
data.text: This location is very small and was initially concerned when I saw the long line the moment I entered.  I was pleasantly surprised seeing the line move so quickly - but even more surprised when I experienced the very friendly service. In fact, this is likely the best customer service experience I have ever had at any Dairy Queen. The vanilla soft serve cone was yummy too. Will definitely return when I am back in the area.

data.title: Blizzards!!
data.text:
I have not been to a DQ for a long time. And on a hot Florida day a blizzard hit the spot. This DQ has 32 seats for you and your friends to sit down after a game or movie to enjoy a cold treat. 
The place was clean and the staff were friendly. The blizzards were made fast and were thick. Will come back.

data.title: is this a part time business?
data.text: felt like having a Mr Misty, so went in and their machine for freezing ice was broken...???  In a chain store?  Our next pick apparently also needed the same machine so we ended up with a bunch of dipped cones....

data.title: A Cool & Creamy Treat
data.text: Treat yourself to an ice cream cone, sundae, blizzard, or several other delicious choices at Jupiter Dairy Queen...one of our favorite ice cream stops!!  A great stop all year long, but especially a welcome destination on these warm spring & summer days & nights. Just don't fill up on dinner or you'll miss a delicious treat...or just get something to take home...but don't miss your cool & creamy treat at Jupiter Dairy Queen on Indiantown Rd & Alt. A1A.

data.title: A Treat With A Smile!
data.text:
Stopped in for a Dairy Queen Cone. I am soooo impressed with the courteous, prompt and thorough service.  And the shop was very very clean.
Even though the young cashier needed help making change, she had a smile on her face and so did her manager who helped her.

data.title: The staff is friendly...
data.text: DQ is DQ!  This one is busy and the gang that work there aim to please you (the customer). They really do their very best to get it right.

data.title: It's not only for ice cream
data.text: This is a smaller DQ so they don't have a grill to do burgers, but you can get hot dogs/chili cheese dogs, chicken strips/sandwiches, bbq pulled chicken and chicken strip wraps. Their  special is a great value for the money.  Add fries, a drink and a sundae to complete your chicken or dog all for $5.00!  You can't go wrong.  I will also add that every time that I've been in the service was great.  Very friendly and very quick.

data.title: Great ice cream
data.text: Hot fudge sundaes like when I was a kid!  Jen is friendly & always greets you with a smile. We go with friends and get dilly bars to go!!!

data.title: Great family spot
data.text:
This is not a grill and chill, which is my favorite fast food stop if I have to do fast food.  They do serve some "real" food like chicken and bbq and hot dogs, etc.  But you really come for the ice cream. 

 You can't go wrong with the latest blizzard flavors or a classic like the banana split. 

 After dozens of visits, I have found the service to be top notch here in regards to friendliness.  Sometimes they seem understaffed and so the service isn't lightening fast.
